metatags.twitter:title: Oregon Passes Comprehensive Data Privacy Law
metatags.og:title: Oregon Passes Comprehensive Data Privacy Law | White & Case LLP
metatags.og:description: On July 18, 2023, Oregon Governor Tina Kotek signed into law Senate Bill 619 (the "Oregon Consumer Privacy Act"), Oregon's new state consumer privacy law, which will become effective July 1, 2024. Oregon now joins California, Utah, Colorado, Connecticut, Virginia, Iowa, Indiana, Tennessee, Montana, Texas, and Florida, (together, "US State Data Privacy Laws") as states with their own consumer privacy laws. Many state legislatures have been quite active in enacting state data privacy laws this year.
